From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 19:15:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] misc: keep Fruit Jam HCD EOP alive after RX

Pico-PIO-USB/wili8jam leaves the EOP detector running across host
transactions and only disables the RX state machine after receiving a packet.
The Fruit Jam Linux HCD setup path now has an RX-only Pico-style receive tail,
but the shared receive helper used by IN data and status handshakes still
stopped EOP after every packet.

Keep EOP alive in the generic receive finish path too.  We still record the
diagnostic RX state first, then disable/clear RX and clear stale IRQ state
before the next token.  This moves the remaining EP0 control phases closer to
the known-working wili8jam transaction lifecycle.
---
 drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c | 12 +++++++-----
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c b/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
--- a/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
+++ b/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
@@ -726,13 +726,14 @@ static void fj_usbhost_pio_finish_receive(struct fruitjam_usbhost *uh,
 					  int ret, u32 len)
 {
 	/*
-	 * Preserve the receive diagnostics first.  Then match Pico-PIO-USB's
-	 * transaction tail by leaving RX idle with no stale FIFO/IRQ state for
-	 * the next SETUP/IN/OUT retry.
+	 * Preserve the receive diagnostics first.  Then match the
+	 * Pico-PIO-USB/wili8jam transaction tail: disable and clear RX, but
+	 * leave the EOP detector running between EP0 phases.
 	 */
 	fj_usbhost_pio_sm_disable(uh, uh->sm_rx);
 	fj_usbhost_pio_record_rx(uh, ret, len);
-	fj_usbhost_pio_disable_receive(uh);
+	fj_usbhost_pio_sm_clear_fifos(uh, uh->sm_rx);
+	fj_usbhost_pio_clear_rx_irq(uh);
 }
 
 static void fj_usbhost_pio_prepare_receive_after_tx(struct fruitjam_usbhost *uh)
